<title>Mutable Objects</title>


<introduction>
<p>
<idx><h>String class</h></idx>
<idx><h>type</h><h>String</h></idx>
As you learned in the previous chapter, an <em>object</em> is a collection of data that provides a set of methods.
For example, a <c>String</c> is a collection of characters that provides methods like <c>charAt</c> and <c>substring</c>.
</p>

<p>
This chapter explores two new types of objects: <c>Point</c> and <c>Rectangle</c>.
You'll see how to write methods that take objects as parameters and produce objects as return values.
You will also look at the source code for the Java library.
</p>
